1st bodybuilding show in the books. (First of many)

RESULTS:

🥇 Classic Physique True Novice
🥇 Classic Physique Novice
🥇 Classic Physique Open
🥇 Classic Physique Novice OVR 
✅ Qualified for nationals

Gave a good effort for Open OVR but we came up short to a guy who definitely deserved the W. I’m happy to have won my open class considering I was 20lbs under the weight limit. Also scored myself a couple physique placements as well (lineups were stacked)

Ultimately one of the best experiences of my entire life. I’d like to thank @philheathclassic and @npcusatexas for putting on such a top notch event, the turnout was unreal. I’d also like to thank my coach @d.lliam_ford for convincing me to do classic and teaching me how to pose. And most importantly my family and friends for coming out and supporting me. Moving forward the goal is to go pro as a Classic Physique competitor. Can’t wait to get do it again. For now, it’s officially off-season. Time to grow.

Off-season is hitting different. 😅 sitting at 230, currently reccomping before making another big push for size later this year. It’s always a particularly hard mental battle for me to get comfortable with extra bodyfat in the off-season. Coming from being in the worst point of my life 2 years ago being 270lbs overweight and depressed, I’ve found that I feel a lot better physically and mentally at lower body fat percentages. With that said I know I’ll never be able to accomplish my dreams if I don’t make sacrifices from time to time. That’s what it takes to be great. Anyone can be good at something, but no one ever became great without sacrificing nearly everything for their dream. That’s something most people (understandably) lack the willpower to go through. This shit ain’t for the mentally sane. But I’d rather be crazy mf anyway.
